  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This project aims at examining the following hypotheses:

        -  Treatment with NADA and clonidine reduces intensity of withdrawal symptoms to a greater
           extent than treatment with clonidine.

        -  Opioid withdrawal improves pain, physical and mental functioning and reduces opioid
           consumption 3 months and 1 year after withdrawal.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
